Finalize the story's structure before it becomes passages. Two jobs, both additions
(the topology is frozen — nothing moves, nothing is deleted):

VISION: {{ vision.genre }}, {{ vision.tone }}. Themes: {{ vision.themes | join("; ") }}.

{% if needs %}
RESIDUE BEATS (required). Where a subplot's paths rejoin, the choice must still be
felt. For each convergence below, write a short flag-gated mood-setter per side: one
beat that establishes how the world feels for a player who took that path, placed
just before the storylines rejoin. 1-2 sentences, present tense, mood not plot — it
must not advance, reveal, or decide anything.
{% for n in needs %}
- {{ n.dilemma.id }} (residue: light{% if n.need.world %}; in the world of {{ n.need.world }}{% endif %}) rejoins at {% for c in n.rejoin %}{{ c.id }} — "{{ c.summary }}"{% if not loop.last %} / {% endif %}{% endfor %}
{% for path, flag in n.need.path_flags.items() %}
  - path {{ path }} (its truth: {{ flag }}) arrives from: {{ n.tails[path].summary }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}
Emit >=1 residue entry per convergence above (one per path is better when both
sides carry a distinct mood). Each entry: {"dilemma", "path", "id": "beat:slug",
"summary", "entities": [...]}; when a convergence names a world, echo it as
"world" exactly (a nested story rejoins once per world — each world needs its
own beats, colored by that world's truth).
{% endif %}
{% if long_runs %}
FALSE BRANCHES (cadence). The story's real choices — its dilemmas — are
guaranteed elsewhere; these stretches run several scenes without ANY choice,
which reads as a book, not a game. Keep the reader's hands on the wheel: fork
an edge roughly every 3-5 beats of a run with a cosmetic diamond — two arms
that are different flavors of the same forward motion, rejoining immediately.
An arm is one 1-sentence beat, plus an optional "followup" beat when its
flavor genuinely needs a breath more room. Arms must differ in texture
(where you look, who you pass, what you overhear), never in consequence.
{% for run in long_runs %}
- linear run: {{ run | join(" -> ") }}
{% endfor %}
Each entry: {"before": beat id, "after": its successor in the same run,
"arms": [{"id", "summary", "entities", "followup": {"id", "summary",
"entities"} or omit}, x2]}. A long run may take several diamonds on
different edges. Leave a stretch unforked only when it must stay unbroken —
the approach to an ending, the immediate aftermath of a point of no return.
{% endif %}
